    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting, but saying it was a \"strategic success\" because it toppled Gaddafi seems a bit contradictory if you follow it up by saying it led to chaos and extremist groups. if the goal was stability in the region, wouldn't the actual outcome be considered a failure? it feels like you're framing the regime change as the win regardless of the actual mess that followed.",
